"12:61:2" : {s: 12, a: 61, w: 2, r: "رود", t: "سَنُرَٰوِدُ", l: "رَٰوَدُ", lc: 8, tl: "sanurāwidu", lb: "প্ররোচিত করা, প্রলব্ধ করা",e: "We will try to get permission", b: "1", i: "kami akan membujuk", f: 1, rm: "to seek, ask a thing gently, search (for food), go to and fro in a pasture, go round about. iradatun - will, free will. mirwad - axle of a pully. rawada - to long after, desire, seduce, entice, seduce against the will (with an) as in 12:126. yuridu - he wishes, intends. It is used as an auxiliary verb as in 18:77. The word iradah is used for power and capacity with reference to subjugation as well as to option and choice. ruwaidan - for a little while, go gently (according to some grammarians the word is a diminutive form of which verbal noun is not in use, it is used as sing. plu. f. m.).", ag: "سين المستقبل وفعل مضارع صيغة ٣", eg: "Future sa and Verb Imperfect 3rd form", tag: "V", pos: "V", att: "IMPF", qual: "(III)", deg: "1", gen: "", num: "P", mood: "", lu: "أَرَادَ"},
